          "Recommendation types",
          "Evaluation",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "E-Learning",
          "Hybrid",
          "Exercise Recommendations",
          "3879 ASSIST09 learners, 2119 EdNet learners, 17886 ASSIST12 learners, 19113 ASSIST13 learners, 821 BePKT learners, 120 learners for User Study",
          "Assistments, EdNet and BePKT",
          "Student-Exerrcise Interactions, Exercise Metadata",
          "Base recommenders’ weights randomly/init default; add two heads: RL head and contrastive head; a pre-trained DKT supplies the reward signal (dynamic reward)",
          "After each interaction, the state is updated and the RL head optimizes cumulative reward (long-term needs). The contrastive head updates representations using augmented positives/negatives; DKT-based reward tracks changes in knowledge mastery (dynamic reward).",
          "Three data augmentations (mask, permute, replace) used for contrastive pairs; ablation varies augmentation ratios (0.1–0.9). Assist09 & EdNet_small used in these tests; excluded from user study due to insufficient content info.",
          "Top-K exercises",
          "AST09\n{Hit-Rate@10: 0.19844 - RCL4ER SASRec, NDCG@10: 0.13070 - RCL4ER SASRec, Hit-Rate@20: 0.30901 - RCL4ER SASRec, NDCG@20: 0.15177 - RCL4ER Bert4Rec, Hit-Rate@50: 0.51787 - RCL4ER NltNet, NDCG@50: 0.19212 - RCL4ER Bert4Rec, L_G: 0.548 - RCL4ER SASRec}\n\nEdNet\n{Hit-Rate@10: 0.19844 - RCL4ER Bert4Rec, NDCG@10: 0.16330 - RCL4ER Bert4Rec, Hit-Rate@20: 0.22596 - RCL4ER Bert4Rec, NDCG@20: 0.16476 - RCL4ER Bert4Rec, Hit-Rate@50: 0.27193 - RCL4ER Bert4Rec, NDCG@50: 0.17379 - RCL4ER Bert4Rec, L_G: 0.539 - RCL4ER GRU}\n\nAST12\n{Hit-Rate@10: 0.36043- RCL4ER SASRec, NDCG@10: 0.29793 - RCL4ER SASRec, Hit-Rate@20: 0.43080 - RCL4ER NltNet, NDCG@20: 0.31528 - RCL4ER Bert4Rec, Hit-Rate@50: 0.57294 - RCL4ER Bert4Rec, NDCG@50: 0.34314 - RCL4ER Bert4Rec, L_G: 0.518 - RCL4ER NltNet}\n\nAST13\n{Hit-Rate@10: 0.227458 - RCL4ER SASRec, NDCG@10: 0.21507 - RCL4ER SASRec, Hit-Rate@20: 0.34640 - RCL4ER SASRec, NDCG@20: 0.23306 - RCL4ER SASRec, Hit-Rate@50: 0.51785 - RCL4ER NltNet, NDCG@50: 0.26296 - RCL4ER NltNet, L_G: 0.521 - RCL4ER NltNet}\n\nUser Study\n{Str_weak_T1: 3.242 vs 2.683, Str_weak_T2: 3.016 vs 2.658, Re_his_T1: 3.316 vs 2.825, Re_his_T2: 3.125 vs 2.850, Exer_diff_T1: 3.192 vs 3.0, Exer_diff_T2: 3.183 vs 3.041, Abi_impro_T1: 3.233 vs 2.883 vs Abi_immpro_T2: 3.042 vs 2.758}",
          "Architecture: model-agnostic RL+CL wrapper; DKT-guided reward aligns recs with knowledge change. Results: improves ranking (HR@10) and learning gain vs. base sequential recommenders; supports classroom/OJ use and teacher oversight.",
          "Data needs: relies on rich exercise metadata; some public datasets lack content detail (not used for expert judgment). \n\nCompute: RL+CL training adds cost. \n\nScope: focuses on sequential recommenders; not a KG method; no explicit classical KT baseline comparison (BKT/DKT etc. are not benchmarked as recommenders).\n\nUser study evaluated essencially by 2 programmers only - small n."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 8
    }
  ],
